# Frontend Component Patterns

Consistent structure for React components using TypeScript and CSS Modules.

## Component File Structure

Each component MUST follow this three-file structure:

```
ComponentName/
├── ComponentName.tsx           # Component implementation
├── ComponentName.module.css    # Scoped CSS module
└── index.ts                    # Barrel export
```

## Component Implementation

### TypeScript Interface

```typescript
import React from "react";
import styles from "./ComponentName.module.css";

export interface ComponentNameProps {
	// Props definition
	children: React.ReactNode;
	variant?: "primary" | "secondary";
	size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
	className?: string;
	onClick?: () => void;
}
```

### Component Definition

````typescript
/**
 * ComponentName - Brief description
 *
 * Usage:
 * ```tsx
 * <ComponentName variant="primary" size="md">
 *   Content here
 * </ComponentName>
 * ```
 */
export const ComponentName: React.FC<ComponentNameProps> = ({ children, variant = "primary", size = "md", className, onClick }) => {
	return (
		<div className={`${styles.container} ${styles[variant]} ${styles[size]} ${className || ""}`} onClick={onClick}>
			{children}
		</div>
	);
};

export default ComponentName;
````

## CSS Modules

Use CSS Modules for scoped styling:

```css
/* ComponentName.module.css */

.container {
	/* Base styles */
	display: flex;
	align-items: center;
}

/* Variants */
.primary {
	background-color: var(--primary-color);
	color: white;
}

.secondary {
	background-color: var(--secondary-color);
	color: white;
}

/* Sizes */
.sm {
	padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
	font-size: 0.875rem;
}

.md {
	padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
	font-size: 1rem;
}

.lg {
	padding: 1rem 2rem;
	font-size: 1.125rem;
}

/* States */
.container:hover {
	opacity: 0.9;
}

.container:disabled {
	opacity: 0.5;
	cursor: not-allowed;
}
```

## Barrel Exports

Each component directory MUST include an `index.ts` file:

```typescript
// index.ts
export { ComponentName } from "./ComponentName";
export type { ComponentNameProps } from "./ComponentName";
```

This enables clean imports:

```typescript
// CORRECT
import { ComponentName } from "@/components/ui/ComponentName";

// INCORRECT
import { ComponentName } from "@/components/ui/ComponentName/ComponentName";
```

## Component Types

### UI Components (`components/ui/`)

Base reusable components with no business logic:

- Button
- Input
- Card
- Modal
- Dropdown
- Checkbox
- Spinner

Characteristics:

- Generic and reusable
- Accept styling through className prop
- Minimal internal state
- No API calls or business logic

### Common Components (`components/common/`)

Shared components with some business logic:

- EmptyState
- ErrorBoundary
- LoadingSpinner
- SuccessMessage

Characteristics:

- Application-specific but reusable
- May include default content/styling
- Can have internal state
- No external data fetching

### Layout Components (`components/layouts/`)

Page structure components:

- AppLayout
- AuthLayout
- LandingLayout
  - Navbar
  - Footer

Characteristics:

- Define page structure
- Handle navigation
- May integrate with context
- Can fetch global data

## Props Patterns

### Required vs Optional Props

```typescript
export interface ComponentProps {
	// Required props (no default)
	id: string;
	title: string;

	// Optional props (with defaults)
	variant?: "primary" | "secondary";
	size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
	isLoading?: boolean;

	// Optional props (no defaults)
	description?: string;
	onClick?: () => void;
	className?: string;
}
```

### Extending HTML Element Props

```typescript
export interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
	variant?: "primary" | "secondary";
	isLoading?: boolean;
	// Custom props
}

export const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps> = ({
	variant = "primary",
	isLoading,
	children,
	className,
	disabled,
	...props // Rest of HTML button props
}) => {
	return (
		<button className={`${styles.button} ${styles[variant]} ${className || ""}`} disabled={disabled || isLoading} {...props}>
			{isLoading ? <Spinner /> : children}
		</button>
	);
};
```

## State Management

### Local State

```typescript
import { useState } from 'react';

export const Component: React.FC = () => {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
  const [value, setValue] = useState('');

  return (
    // Component JSX
  );
};
```

### Context

```typescript
import { useContext } from "react";
import { AuthContext } from "@/context/AuthContext";

export const Component: React.FC = () => {
	const { user, isAuthenticated } = useContext(AuthContext);

	if (!isAuthenticated) {
		return <div>Please log in</div>;
	}

	return <div>Welcome, {user.email}</div>;
};
```

### Custom Hooks

```typescript
import { useAuth } from "@/hooks/useAuth";
import { useDebounce } from "@/hooks/useDebounce";

export const Component: React.FC = () => {
	const { user } = useAuth();
	const [search, setSearch] = useState("");
	const debouncedSearch = useDebounce(search, 500);

	// Use debouncedSearch for API calls
};
```

## Event Handlers

```typescript
export const Component: React.FC = () => {
	const handleClick = () => {
		// Handle click
	};

	const handleSubmit = (e: React.FormEvent) => {
		e.preventDefault();
		// Handle form submission
	};

	const handleChange = (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
		setValue(e.target.value);
	};

	return (
		<form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
			<input onChange={handleChange} />
			<button onClick={handleClick}>Submit</button>
		</form>
	);
};
```

## Conditional Rendering

```typescript
export const Component: React.FC<Props> = ({ isLoading, error, data }) => {
	if (isLoading) {
		return <LoadingSpinner />;
	}

	if (error) {
		return <ErrorBoundary error={error} />;
	}

	if (!data || data.length === 0) {
		return <EmptyState message="No data available" />;
	}

	return (
		<div>
			{data.map((item) => (
				<div key={item.id}>{item.name}</div>
			))}
		</div>
	);
};
```

## CSS Variable Usage

Use CSS variables defined in `styles/variables.css`:

```css
.container {
	color: var(--text-primary);
	background-color: var(--bg-primary);
	border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
	border-radius: var(--radius-md);
	padding: var(--spacing-md);
}
```

## Responsive Design

```css
.container {
	width: 100%;
}

/* Mobile first */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
	.container {
		width: 50%;
	}
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
	.container {
		width: 33.333%;
	}
}
```

Or use the `useMediaQuery` hook:

```typescript
import { useMediaQuery } from "@/hooks/useMediaQuery";

export const Component: React.FC = () => {
	const isMobile = useMediaQuery("(max-width: 768px)");

	return <div>{isMobile ? <MobileView /> : <DesktopView />}</div>;
};
```

## Accessibility

```typescript
export const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps> = ({ children, isLoading, ...props }) => {
	return (
		<button aria-label={props["aria-label"]} aria-busy={isLoading} aria-disabled={props.disabled} {...props}>
			{children}
		</button>
	);
};
```

## Documentation

Each component MUST include:

- JSDoc comment with description
- Usage example in JSDoc
- Props interface with comments for complex props

````typescript
/**
 * Modal Component - Displays content in an overlay dialog
 *
 * Features:
 * - Backdrop click to close
 * - Escape key to close
 * - Focus trap
 * - Smooth animations
 *
 * Usage:
 * ```tsx
 * <Modal isOpen={isOpen} onClose={handleClose} title="My Modal">
 *   <p>Modal content goes here</p>
 * </Modal>
 * ```
 */
export const Modal: React.FC<ModalProps> = ({ ... }) => {
  // Implementation
};
````

## Testing Considerations

Structure components for testability:

1. Extract complex logic to custom hooks
2. Accept data as props (avoid internal fetching when possible)
3. Use data-testid attributes for testing
4. Keep components focused (single responsibility)

```typescript
export const Component: React.FC<Props> = ({ data, onAction }) => {
	return (
		<div data-testid="component-container">
			{data.map((item) => (
				<div key={item.id} data-testid={`item-${item.id}`}>
					{item.name}
				</div>
			))}
		</div>
	);
};
```
